Currently thinking back on my pregnancy experience and I’m very happy I was honest about what I went through. These pictures represents my pregnancy in a nut shell. I had the worse case of thrush. My tongue was swollen , the side of my lips were cut, I couldnt eat (vomited for 39 weeks STRAIGHT), I cried EVERYDAY and I felt DISGUSTING! To say my pregnancy traumatized me is a understatement but I want women who are looking forward to have a child know that it’s okay to not feel great in your pregnancy! Everyone’s experience of pregnancy is very different and that’s okay. Also to the IVF moms please know that it’s okay to express how hard your experience can be! Holding back on how you really feel about your pregnancy can affect you tremendously! Postpartum Depression is real!!!! I want another child (no time soon) but idk if it’s worth trying to have the same experience All over again because I thought I was gonna die while being pregnant. DONT LET ANYONE TELL YOU HOW TO FEEL!
